The '''<tt>su</tt>''' ('''s'''ubstitute '''u'''ser) command can be used to impersonate other users on the system. <tt>su</tt> is provided by the {{Package|sys-apps/shadow}} package. It is also included with the {{Package|sys-apps/util-linux}} package, but it is disabled in the ebuild to prevent a file collision with {{Package|sys-apps/shadow}}.

