== Usage ==

<tt>su</tt> will run commands as root by default. Since not specifying a username will cause <tt>su</tt> to ask for root privileges, the following command will run as root and halt the system:
{{Cmd|su -c 'shutdown -h now'}}

{{Note|It is best practice to encapsulate the commands following the <code>-c</code> option with either single or double quotes.}}

It is also possible to specify a user other than root to substitute commands. The following example will run the command <tt>echo</tt> as the user larry:
{{Cmd|su -c 'echo "Moo to the Gentoo Wiki reader out there!"' larry}}

